            <div class="container">
                <div class="question">
                    <button class="accordion">
                        Joint Probability Distribution and Expected Value
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="panel">
                        <h5>Question:</h5>
                        <p>
                            Suppose that \( X \) and \( Y \) are independent random variables having the following joint
                            probability distribution:
                        </p>
                        <p style="text-align: center;">
                            <table border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse; margin: auto; width: 50%; text-align: center;">
                                <thead>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th>\( f(x, y) \)</th>
                                        <th colspan="2">\( x \)</th>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th>\( y \)</th>
                                        <th>2</th>
                                        <th>4</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>1</td>
                                        <td>0.10</td>
                                        <td>0.15</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>3</td>
                                        <td>0.20</td>
                                        <td>0.30</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>5</td>
                                        <td>0.10</td>
                                        <td>0.15</td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Find:
                            <br>(a) \( E(2X - 3Y) \)
                            <br>(b) \( E(XY) \)
                        </p>
                        <div class="solution">
                            <h5>Solution:</h5>
                            <p><strong>(a) \( E(2X - 3Y) \):</strong></p>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.2em; text-align: center;">
                                Using linearity of expectation: <br>
                                \( E(2X - 3Y) = 2E(X) - 3E(Y) \)
                            </p>
                            <p>Step-by-step:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>\( E(X) = \sum_x x \cdot P(X=x) \)</li>
                                <li>\( = 2 \cdot (0.10 + 0.20 + 0.10) + 4 \cdot (0.15 + 0.30 + 0.15) = 2.80 \)</li>
                                <li>\( E(Y) = \sum_y y \cdot P(Y=y) \)</li>
                                <li>\( = 1 \cdot (0.10 + 0.15) + 3 \cdot (0.20 + 0.30) + 5 \cdot (0.10 + 0.15) = 3.25 \)</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.2em; text-align: center;">
                                \( E(2X - 3Y) = 2(2.80) - 3(3.25) = -4.15 \)
                            </p>
                            <p><strong>(b) \( E(XY) \):</strong></p>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.2em; text-align: center;">
                                Since \( X \) and \( Y \) are independent: <br>
                                \( E(XY) = E(X) \cdot E(Y) \)
                            </p>
                            <p style="font-size: 1.2em; text-align: center;">
                                From part (a): \( E(X) = 2.80, E(Y) = 3.25 \) <br>
                                \( E(XY) = 2.80 \cdot 3.25 = 9.10 \)
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
